can interpret common price charts for your own

274
00:09:27,670 --> 00:09:28,450
technical analysis.

275
00:09:28,610 --> 00:09:31,030
So next, let's talk about support and resistance

276
00:09:31,030 --> 00:09:33,270
lines and how to derive and interpret them

277
00:09:33,270 --> 00:09:35,050
for your very own strategy.

278
00:09:35,190 --> 00:09:38,370
Well, support and resistant lines are horizontal lines

279
00:09:38,370 --> 00:09:40,550
that you can draw onto your price chart.

280
00:09:40,550 --> 00:09:43,910
Support shows the lowest price at which investors

281
00:09:43,910 --> 00:09:45,630
are willing to buy that asset.

282
00:09:46,050 --> 00:09:48,610
This signals when buyers show the most demand

283
00:09:48,610 --> 00:09:49,770
for an asset.

284
00:09:49,870 --> 00:09:52,510
When you see an asset continually bouncing off

285
00:09:52,510 --> 00:09:54,550
a specific price, this is support.

286
00:09:54,670 --> 00:09:56,990
Let's say you're trying to forecast prices for

287
00:09:56,990 --> 00:09:57,730
the next month.

288
00:09:58,050 --> 00:09:59,710
You might look at the lowest price point

289
00:09:59,710 --> 00:10:02,090
from the previous month and label this your

290
00:10:02,090 --> 00:10:02,950
support level.

291
00:10:03,130 --> 00:10:05,230
This way, if and when your stock or

292
00:10:05,230 --> 00:10:07,590
crypto dips to below that price point the

293
00:10:07,590 --> 00:10:11,030
following month, you can anticipate that an upwards

294
00:10:11,030 --> 00:10:12,550
trend may be coming.

295
00:10:12,670 --> 00:10:14,930
Resistance, on the other hand, shows the highest

296
00:10:14,930 --> 00:10:17,710
price at which investors will usually stop buying

297
00:10:17,710 --> 00:10:20,030
and instead begin selling that asset.

298
00:10:20,230 --> 00:10:22,250
This can signal that there are more buyers

299
00:10:22,250 --> 00:10:24,970
than sellers in the market at that specific

300
00:10:24,970 --> 00:10:26,950
price, meaning that the asset will have a

301
00:10:26,950 --> 00:10:29,470
harder time passing through this price point.

302
00:10:29,570 --> 00:10:31,330
In your analysis, you might see that support

303
00:10:31,330 --> 00:10:33,730
and resistance lines don't really change from period

304
00:10:33,730 --> 00:10:34,130
to period.

305
00:10:34,250 --> 00:10:36,190
This happens when the majority of buyers and

306
00:10:36,190 --> 00:10:38,870
sellers tend to group around the prevailing support

307
00:10:38,870 --> 00:10:40,110
and resistance lines.

308
00:10:40,230 --> 00:10:41,710
And this could lead to what we call

309
00:10:41,710 --> 00:10:44,170
trading sideways, where the price doesn't change a

310
00:10:44,170 --> 00:10:45,870
whole lot over a period of time.

311
00:10:45,950 --> 00:10:46,890
Now, what you want to look out for

312
00:10:46,890 --> 00:10:49,690
are price movements that break away from support

313
00:10:49,690 --> 00:10:50,890
and resistance lines.

314
00:10:50,990 --> 00:10:53,130
Take, for example, our ADA chart from last

315
00:10:53,130 --> 00:10:53,430
month.

316
00:10:53,530 --> 00:10:56,510
Notice how from September 15th through October 18th,

317
00:10:56,550 --> 00:10:58,390
there was a steady decline in the resistance

318
00:10:58,390 --> 00:11:01,210
line, meaning that investors were finding lower and

319
00:11:01,210 --> 00:11:04,010
lower prices too expensive to buy.

320
00:11:04,090 --> 00:11:06,130
We saw the resistance line drop from $2

321
00:11:06,130 --> 00:11:08,470
.6 down to $2.3 and then continue

322
00:11:08,470 --> 00:11:11,430
to dip around $2.1. So at least

323
00:11:11,430 --> 00:11:13,890
for this short period that we're measuring, the

324
00:11:13,890 --> 00:11:16,750
price at which there was an oversupply of

325
00:11:16,750 --> 00:11:19,030
ADA kept getting lower and lower.

326
00:11:19,450 --> 00:11:21,490
This might lead an analyst to believe that

327
00:11:21,490 --> 00:11:23,830
there would be a steep correction coming in

328
00:11:23,830 --> 00:11:24,470
this asset.

329
00:11:24,550 --> 00:11:25,870
Next, we need to talk about formations.

330
00:11:26,130 --> 00:11:28,830
Formations are patterns in the price movement of

331
00:11:28,830 --> 00:11:30,350
an asset on its chart.

332
00:11:30,470 --> 00:11:33,970
Formations are amazing because this is what allow

333
00:11:33,970 --> 00:11:36,570
us to identify the most likely direction an

334
00:11:36,570 --> 00:11:39,050
asset is headed to, as well as the

335
00:11:39,050 --> 00:11:41,170
most likely price it will stop at after

336
00:11:41,170 --> 00:11:42,870
breaking through that formation.

337
00:11:43,050 --> 00:11:44,550
In the same image, you will see a

338
00:11:44,550 --> 00:11:46,770
yellow circle and a green circle.

339
00:11:46,870 --> 00:11:48,790
The yellow circle is the moment this asset

340
00:11:48,790 --> 00:11:50,370
broke out of the formation.

341
00:11:50,630 --> 00:11:52,770
Most traders, get a listen here, most traders

342
00:11:52,770 --> 00:11:55,590
will make the mistake of entering a long

343
00:11:55,590 --> 00:11:58,390
or buy position at the moment of breakout.

344
00:11:58,650 --> 00:12:01,110
This is a huge but very common mistake

345
00:12:01,110 --> 00:12:02,110
new traders make.

346
00:12:02,170 --> 00:12:03,970
They assume that since it broke out of

347
00:12:03,970 --> 00:12:07,110
the formation, this verifies the formation that they

348
00:12:07,110 --> 00:12:09,670
drew, it verifies that it's accurate, and verifies

349
00:12:09,670 --> 00:12:11,850
that the asset will go directly to their

350
00:12:11,850 --> 00:12:12,550
price target.

351
00:12:12,650 --> 00:12:15,050
But it's an extremely important practice to be

352
00:12:15,050 --> 00:12:18,190
patient here and wait for the confirmation bounce.

353
00:12:18,490 --> 00:12:20,870
An example of this is the green circle.

354
00:12:21,010 --> 00:12:23,430
The price bounces off of our previous resistance

355
00:12:23,430 --> 00:12:26,670
line, confirming that this resistance no longer has

356
00:12:26,670 --> 00:12:27,610
the same effect.

357
00:12:27,930 --> 00:12:30,730
The confirmation bounce should be the best moment

358
00:12:30,730 --> 00:12:32,290
to enter in your trade.

359
00:12:32,330 --> 00:12:34,370
If it bounces to the upside, you would

360
00:12:34,370 --> 00:12:35,590
enter a long position.

361
00:12:35,950 --> 00:12:37,530
If it breaks through to the downside, you

362
00:12:37,530 --> 00:12:39,010
would enter a short position.

363
00:12:39,110 --> 00:12:40,610
Breaking through a pattern just like the trend

364
00:12:40,610 --> 00:12:42,570
lines we just discussed is called a continuation

365
00:12:42,570 --> 00:12:43,290
pattern.

366
00:12:43,410 --> 00:12:45,870
So let's briefly cover a few popular patterns

367
00:12:45,870 --> 00:12:47,570
that you may see referenced.

368
00:12:47,890 --> 00:12:49,410
The pattern that we just looked at could

369
00:12:49,410 --> 00:12:51,370
be referred to as a wedge pattern.

370
00:12:51,510 --> 00:12:53,790
If trend lines had connected in that pattern,

371
00:12:53,890 --> 00:12:55,570
it would be called a pennant pattern.

372
00:12:55,770 --> 00:12:58,490
Flag patterns are two parallel trend lines that

373
00:12:58,490 --> 00:13:00,870
can head upwards, downwards, or sideways.

374
00:13:01,010 --> 00:13:03,190
A cup and handle pattern is when the

375
00:13:03,190 --> 00:13:04,790
price increase has paused.

376
00:13:05,090 --> 00:13:06,890
The bowl shape is then followed by what

377
00:13:06,890 --> 00:13:09,450
looks like a pennant chart pattern, and this

378
00:13:09,450 --> 00:13:11,910
may indicate a further breakout in price.

379
00:13:12,010 --> 00:13:14,030
A head and shoulders trend following an increase

380
00:13:14,030 --> 00:13:16,650
in price may indicate the price will decrease.

381
00:13:16,830 --> 00:13:19,450
A reverse head and shoulders trend following a

382
00:13:19,450 --> 00:13:21,850
decrease in price may indicate that the price

383
00:13:21,850 --> 00:13:22,690
will increase.

384
00:13:22,790 --> 00:13:25,550
Now, it's important to note that humans love

385
00:13:25,550 --> 00:13:28,450
finding patterns in literally anything, and there are

386
00:13:28,450 --> 00:13:30,670
a million chart patterns that can mean different

387
00:13:30,670 --> 00:13:31,010
things.

388
00:13:31,010 --> 00:13:33,190
But this doesn't mean you should expect the

389
00:13:33,190 --> 00:13:34,730
result to always come true.

390
00:13:34,890 --> 00:13:36,530
Again, this just helps paint a more clear

391
00:13:36,530 --> 00:13:38,970
picture, but does not absolutely tell us the

392
00:13:38,970 --> 00:13:39,270
future.

393
00:13:39,430 --> 00:13:41,270
Now that you know when to enter a

394
00:13:41,270 --> 00:13:42,930
trade, let's talk about when you should exit

395
00:13:42,930 --> 00:13:45,070
a trade because this may be even more

396
00:13:45,070 --> 00:13:46,950
important than when you enter a trade.

397
00:13:47,030 --> 00:13:48,670
And this answer may vary because it depends

398
00:13:48,670 --> 00:13:50,430
on whether or not you are trading futures

399
00:13:50,430 --> 00:13:53,590
with leverage or trading spot without leverage.

400
00:13:53,750 --> 00:13:56,130
Leverage is simply borrowing money to use in

401
00:13:56,130 --> 00:13:58,850
a trade to help increase your potential return.

402
00:13:59,170 --> 00:14:01,970
Let's say you've entered a trade When trading

403
00:14:01,970 --> 00:14:04,570
with leverage, you may borrow funds against that

404
00:14:04,570 --> 00:14:04,930
$100.

405
00:14:05,410 --> 00:14:08,370
With 10x leverage, your $100 acts as if

406
00:14:08,370 --> 00:14:09,230
it's $1,000.

407
00:14:09,830 --> 00:14:12,290
So mathematically, when the asset you're trading goes

408
00:14:12,290 --> 00:14:15,050
up 1%, you will actually be 10%

409
00:14:15,050 --> 00:14:15,610
in profit.

410
00:14:15,730 --> 00:14:17,510
However, it's not all good and rosy because

411
00:14:17,510 --> 00:14:19,690
if the trade goes down 1%, you will

412
00:14:19,690 --> 00:14:21,350
be at a 10% loss.

413
00:14:21,570 --> 00:14:23,250
If you lose too much, you will be

414
00:14:23,250 --> 00:14:26,330
liquidated completely, meaning you lose all the funds

415
00:14:26,330 --> 00:14:27,850
that you entered into the trade and you

416
00:14:27,850 --> 00:14:29,030
don't want to be in that position.

417
00:14:29,030 --> 00:14:30,890
So this, of course, is very high risk

418
00:14:30,890 --> 00:14:32,170
and not for beginners.

419
00:14:32,510 --> 00:14:35,170
Now, trading spot is just regular trading with

420
00:14:35,170 --> 00:14:36,650
your own money and no borrowing.

421
00:14:36,750 --> 00:14:38,250
Here you still have the risk of losing

422
00:14:38,250 --> 00:14:40,810
money, but liquidation is not a concern like

423
00:14:40,810 --> 00:14:42,090
it is with leverage.

424
00:14:42,210 --> 00:14:44,030
When trading with leverage, typically you want to

425
00:14:44,030 --> 00:14:46,390
close your trade the moment you hit your

426
00:14:46,390 --> 00:14:47,730
target or just before.

427
00:14:47,830 --> 00:14:49,190
This will prevent you from being hit with

428
00:14:49,190 --> 00:14:50,530
recurring leverage fees.

429
00:14:50,610 --> 00:14:52,210
When you're trading with spot, you don't have

430
00:14:52,210 --> 00:14:54,510
to worry so much about rushing out of

431
00:14:54,510 --> 00:14:54,990
the trade.

432
00:14:55,310 --> 00:14:57,370
So if a trade has surpassed your target,

433
00:14:57,450 --> 00:14:59,390
you can simply hold longer and set up

434
00:14:59,390 --> 00:15:00,890
a trailing stop loss.

435
00:15:01,230 --> 00:15:03,310
Now, a trailing stop loss is a stop

436
00:15:03,310 --> 00:15:05,230
loss tool you can use that will follow

437
00:15:05,230 --> 00:15:07,330
the price of an asset by a dollar

438
00:15:07,330 --> 00:15:09,490
amount of your choice and then close your

439
00:15:09,490 --> 00:15:12,070
trade at the maximum amount of profits possible

440
00:15:12,070 --> 00:15:14,110
completely on autopilot.

441
00:15:14,510 --> 00:15:16,690
Typically, you wouldn't set up a trailing stop

442
00:15:16,690 --> 00:15:19,090
loss until your price target is already hit

443
00:15:19,090 --> 00:15:20,370
and you just want to try and make

444
00:15:20,370 --> 00:15:21,410
a little bit more profit.

445
00:15:21,510 --> 00:15:23,490
Now, speaking of hit, if you appreciate my

446
00:15:23,490 --> 00:15:25,810
efforts in putting together this free course, just

447
00:15:25,810 --> 00:15:27,990
please consider hitting the subscribe button.

448
00:15:27,990 --> 00:15:30,270
It's totally free and you can always change

449
00:15:30,270 --> 00:15:31,150
your mind later.

450
00:15:31,410 --> 00:15:34,070
Now, spotting trends isn't enough on its own.

451
00:15:34,190 --> 00:15:36,110
You also need to evaluate the strength of

452
00:15:36,110 --> 00:15:38,910
a trend because not all trends are created

453
00:15:38,910 --> 00:15:39,370
equally.

454
00:15:39,590 --> 00:15:41,550
So one indicator that we can look at

455
00:15:41,550 --> 00:15:42,770
is trading volume.

456
00:15:42,990 --> 00:15:45,010
This is the total dollar amount traded of

457
00:15:45,010 --> 00:15:45,490
an asset.

458
00:15:45,610 --> 00:15:47,310
Now, it's pretty simple to do this, so

459
00:15:47,310 --> 00:15:48,850
it should be a regular part of your

460
00:15:48,850 --> 00:15:49,670
technical analysis.

461
00:15:50,010 --> 00:15:52,410
The higher the trading volume, the stronger the

462
00:15:52,410 --> 00:15:52,730
trend.

463
00:15:52,890 --> 00:15:53,990
And this makes sense if you think about

464
00:15:53,990 --> 00:15:56,290
it because a trend with 10 million in

465
00:15:56,290 --> 00:15:58,290
volume behind it means much more than a

466
00:15:58,290 --> 00:16:00,130
trend with 1 million in volume behind it.

467
00:16:00,190 --> 00:16:01,530
So it's always good to take a look

468
00:16:01,530 --> 00:16:03,950
at the 24-hour trading volume on days

469
00:16:03,950 --> 00:16:06,490
where the price moved downwards and then compare

470
00:16:06,490 --> 00:16:08,190
this to the trading volume on days where

471
00:16:08,190 --> 00:16:09,270
the price moves upwards.

472
00:16:09,470 --> 00:16:11,970
If you see higher volumes on positive days,

473
00:16:12,030 --> 00:16:13,690
this can tell us that there's a long

474
00:16:13,690 --> 00:16:16,010
-term potential for the asset to continue trending

475
00:16:16,010 --> 00:16:16,450
upwards.

476
00:16:16,730 --> 00:16:18,870
This also helps us evaluate how the market

477
00:16:18,870 --> 00:16:21,210
will react to a sharp drop in price.

478
00:16:21,270 --> 00:16:23,950
If the trading volume during one dip is

479
00:16:23,950 --> 00:16:27,430
larger than another more severe dip later on,

480
00:16:27,730 --> 00:16:29,790
we might determine that the drop in price

481
00:16:29,790 --> 00:16:33,470
does not signify a stronger downwards trend.

482
00:16:33,610 --> 00:16:35,630
Something else to take into consideration is market

483
00:16:35,630 --> 00:16:37,670
cap, which you get by multiplying the current

484
00:16:37,670 --> 00:16:39,830
price of your crypto or stock with the

485
00:16:39,830 --> 00:16:42,390
total supply of the crypto or stock.

486
00:16:42,750 --> 00:16:44,910
Big cap coins and stocks tend to be

487
00:16:44,910 --> 00:16:48,430
more stable because large volume trades have less

488
00:16:48,430 --> 00:16:49,890
of an impact on their prices.

489
00:16:49,970 --> 00:16:51,630
It's hard to move a big ship.

490
00:16:51,750 --> 00:16:53,270
Now, let's move on to a more technical

491
00:16:53,270 --> 00:16:54,690
indicator of price movement.

492
00:16:54,690 --> 00:16:56,730
And one that I use quite regularly.

493
00:16:56,930 --> 00:16:59,510
This is the Relative Strength Index, or RSI

494
00:16:59,510 --> 00:17:00,710
indicator for short.

495
00:17:01,070 --> 00:17:03,369
The RSI of a certain crypto or stock

496
00:17:03,369 --> 00:17:05,490
usually is pretty easy to access.

497
00:17:05,630 --> 00:17:08,349
It's usually displayed just underneath price charts for

498
00:17:08,349 --> 00:17:11,369
the purpose of directly comparing price trends with

499
00:17:11,369 --> 00:17:12,270
the RSI.

500
00:17:12,390 --> 00:17:14,130
It's displayed as a number between 0 and

501
00:17:14,130 --> 00:17:17,290
100, and this number changes continuously based on

502
00:17:17,290 --> 00:17:20,990
trading activity, typically relative to the average gains

503
00:17:20,990 --> 00:17:23,210
in losses over a 14-day period.

504
00:17:23,210 --> 00:17:25,530
This kind of graph is called an oscillator

505
00:17:25,530 --> 00:17:27,770
because the readings always show a number between

506
00:17:27,770 --> 00:17:28,770
0 and 100.

507
00:17:28,930 --> 00:17:30,410
So let's break down how this works.

508
00:17:30,770 --> 00:17:34,050
In basic situations without drastic market moving events,

509
00:17:34,410 --> 00:17:36,670
RSI indicates whether a crypto or any kind

510
00:17:36,670 --> 00:17:39,850
of security is overbought or oversold.

511
00:17:40,230 --> 00:17:42,510
A reading above 70 would tell us that

512
00:17:42,510 --> 00:17:44,830
it's overbought and can signal that a price

513
00:17:44,830 --> 00:17:46,270
correction may happen.

514
00:17:46,350 --> 00:17:49,690
A prolonged RSI above 70 can be interpreted

515
00:17:49,690 --> 00:17:51,670
as some kind of bubble and that the

516
00:17:51,670 --> 00:17:54,850
coming correction could create dramatic losses to the

517
00:17:54,850 --> 00:17:56,610
people who are invested in that asset.

518
00:17:56,970 --> 00:17:59,270
Now, readings under 30 indicate that the security

519
00:17:59,270 --> 00:18:00,390
is oversold.

520
00:18:00,770 --> 00:18:03,370
In other words, the asset may be undervalued,

521
00:18:03,510 --> 00:18:04,970
meaning it could be a good opportunity.

522
00:18:05,430 --> 00:18:07,850
You've probably seen videos where certain cryptos or

523
00:18:07,850 --> 00:18:10,110
stocks are proclaimed to be undervalued.

524
00:18:10,230 --> 00:18:12,290
The RSI indicator was likely one of the

525
00:18:12,290 --> 00:18:14,550
tools used to come to that conclusion, and

526
00:18:14,550 --> 00:18:15,350
now you can use that.

527
00:18:15,370 --> 00:18:16,770
At the water cooler, at work, you can

528
00:18:16,770 --> 00:18:17,630
be like, Hey, you know what?

529
00:18:17,670 --> 00:18:19,190
I think that this stock is undervalued.

530
00:18:19,330 --> 00:18:20,850
You know, you just check the RSI.

531
00:18:20,990 --> 00:18:21,930
It can be that easy.

532
00:18:21,930 --> 00:18:25,070
So there's actually a whole book written about

533
00:18:25,070 --> 00:18:26,370
the Relative Strength Index.

534
00:18:26,470 --> 00:18:28,010
If you want to fully understand it, I

535
00:18:28,010 --> 00:18:30,050
will have this book linked in the description

536
00:18:30,050 --> 00:18:30,850
of this video.

537
00:18:31,030 --> 00:18:32,170
Now we need to talk about the moving

538
00:18:32,170 --> 00:18:32,630
average.

539
00:18:32,770 --> 00:18:34,510
You can calculate this by taking the price

540
00:18:34,510 --> 00:18:36,450
readings of your crypto or stock from the

541
00:18:36,450 --> 00:18:37,770
last X number of days.

542
00:18:37,870 --> 00:18:39,610
The standard is 20, but you can reduce

543
00:18:39,610 --> 00:18:41,710
it to about 5 if your trading strategy

544
00:18:41,710 --> 00:18:42,470
requires it.

545
00:18:42,790 --> 00:18:44,630
So this works by adding up the prices

546
00:18:44,630 --> 00:18:47,650
